                    <BLOCKQUOTE><TABLE border="1"><TBODY><TR><TD><BLOCKQUOTE><TABLE border="1"><TBODY><TR><TD><BLOCKQUOTE><TABLE border="1"><TBODY><TR><TD><BLOCKQUOTE><TABLE border="1"><TBODY><TR><TD><BLOCKQUOTE><TABLE border="1"><TBODY><TR><TD><BLOCKQUOTE><TABLE border="1"><TBODY><TR><TD><BLOCKQUOTE><TABLE border="1"><TBODY><TR><TD><BLOCKQUOTE><TABLE border="1"><TBODY><TR><TD><BLOCKQUOTE><TABLE border="1"><TBODY><TR><TD><BLOCKQUOTE><TABLE border="1"><TBODY><TR><TD>I challenge Voidarix!<BR /><BR />-Blazer the Nuurakh-</TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE></BLOCKQUOTE><BR />Bring it!<BR />*I surround myself in a type of fire-armor (cross between rock and fire)*<BR />*my golem shrinks down to human size, the pure power of the giant version condensed into the small version, making it even more powerful*<BR />*it rushes up to you and punches you multiple times before you can react* </TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE></BLOCKQUOTE><BR />*I am sent crashing into a wall. I use a regeneration disk to repair myself, and get back up*<BR /><BR />-Blazer the Nuurakh- </TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE></BLOCKQUOTE><BR />*he repeats, sending you hurtling back once more*<BR />*I seemingly stand, just watching, as energy swirls around my palms* </TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE></BLOCKQUOTE><BR />*When he hits me, I bring up my staffs. He gets under my control, and I stay a considerable distance from him,just in case*<BR /><BR />-Blazer the Nuurakh- </TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE></BLOCKQUOTE><BR />*as you struggle to keep control over him, I fire twin blasts of energy at you, knocking your staffs out of your hands and breaking your control completely*<BR />*the golem, now very angry, tackles you to the ground*<BR />*I begin charging my energy once again* </TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE></BLOCKQUOTE><BR />OOC: Actually, the staffs don't work that way. Once you're hit with one, you're a goner<BR /><BR />IC: *I order him to attack you* </TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE></BLOCKQUOTE><BR />*it glows green, and he suddenly stands up straight, looks at you, and tackles you to the ground*<BR />(smirks) Did you really think that would work? It is fueled with one of the most powerful substances I have ever encountered, more powerful enought to deflect a simple Vahki attack! <img class="emoticon emoticon-frustrated" id="frustrated" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/frustrated.png" alt="Frustrated" title="Frustrated" /><BR />*I still charge my energy* </TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE></BLOCKQUOTE><BR />*I dodge, and he crashes into a mountain. Since he's so strong, it crumbles and the debris pins him down. I then face you, keeping an eye on the Golem* Bring it on, Makuta!<BR /><BR />-Blazer the Nuurakh- </TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE></BLOCKQUOTE><BR />Fine<BR />*after I have charged my energy so long, a giant torrent of fire, rock, energy, green powder, ice (somehow not melting), and water (somehow not evaporating or putting out the fire)*<BR />*light begins pouring out of the pile of debris. It expands, soon enveloping all the stone. When it disappears, the golem is standing above a pile of ash, twin giant swords in both his hands*<BR />(hulk voice) Who drop montain on Golem!? Golem destroy!!!!<BR />*energy envelops him, and he rushes towards you, the pure strength melting the earth around it* </TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE></BLOCKQUOTE><BR />*I fire a weakening disk at his feet, creating a hole he falls in. His energy makes it harder to climb out, and I run towards you, avoiding the torrent*<BR /><BR />-Blazer the Nuurakh-
                
            
			
